data.description: Ready for a new distinguished owner, this very grand and elaborate estate in Sand Canyon is gated and set on 2.5 flat, usable acres and includes a pool, spa, outdoor kitchen, a barn with exterior recently rebuilt, and ample amounts of space to raise horses. With NO HOA OR MELLO-ROOS, this Tudor style home is adorned with the most exquisite Italian Baroque style woodwork and detailed artistry evident in the ornate crown molding, ceiling medallions, and Italy-imported fireplace mantles. Upon entry through the leaded glass double doors, you’re welcomed into the foyer with vaulted ceilings and ~$300,000 worth of marble from the flooring, baseboards, window and door trims, bathrooms, countertops, and much more. There is another ~$300,000 worth of custom woodwork you’ll see tastefully expressed throughout the home. The first level includes two bedrooms, 3/4 bath finished with honey onyx marble, living room, family room, dining room, bonus room, laundry room, and chef’s kitchen with an island and granite countertops, stainless steel sink, Bosch dishwasher, range hood, microwave, built-in KitchenAid refrigerator, and a Thermador Professional slide in range. On the second level through leaded glass double doors, you’ll find your jaw-dropping executive office/library with coffered ceilings, elegant white Italian fireplace, and the most stunningly detailed custom woodwork and artistry layered throughout. Upstairs you also have two more secondary bedrooms with walk-in closets, two more marble 3/4 bathrooms, and a primary suite with its own fireplace, custom built walk-in closet, 3 hidden storage areas, and a captivating, luxurious bathroom covered in marble with spiral pillars flanking a raised soaking jacuzzi tub beside the frameless glass walk-in shower. Coming off the primary suite and executive office, you have an expansive balcony overlooking your 2.5 acre estate surrounded by beautiful oak trees. Your 3 car garage has epoxy flooring, plenty of cabinetry for storage, and a tankless water heater. Newer windows and roof having just been replaced a few years ago! Close to the Sand Canyon Country Club, Sulphur Springs elementary school, the 14 freeway, and plenty of restaurants and businesses, this spectacular estate is truly one-of-a-kind and you must see it in person to appreciate the artistry and pride of ownership that is evident throughout this home!
